---
import Page from '../../layouts/PageEn.astro';
import { url } from '../../utils/url';
---

<Page
  title="Big Tech Files — English edition (preview)"
  description="Big Tech Files: 33 documented Big Tech cases — privacy, security, citizen rights. Reference base for journalists, lawyers, academics."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero__grid">
      <div class="hero__body">
        <p class="hero__tagline">Sprawy Big Techu — Polish edition</p>
        <h1 class="hero__title">Big Tech<br />Files.</h1>
        <div class="hero__lead">
          <p class="hero__lead-thesis">Not exceptions. A pattern.</p>
          <p class="hero__lead-scope">Abuse. Data extraction. Broken law.</p>
          <p class="hero__lead-numbers">33 cases. 12 companies. 480 sources.</p>
          <p class="hero__lead-stamp">Documented.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a href={url('/')} class="btn btn--primary">← Polish edition</a>
          <span class="hero__notice">
            English edition in preview. Full translation planned for Phase 4.
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="hero__aside" aria-label="Key figures">
        <div class="hero__fact">
          <p class="hero__fact-value">€1.2 bn</p>
          <p class="hero__fact-label">Record GDPR fine</p>
          <p class="hero__fact-desc">Meta Ireland, 2023. For transferring European data to the US.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__fact">
          <p class="hero__fact-value">0.7%</p>
          <p class="hero__fact-label">of Meta's annual revenue</p>
          <p class="hero__fact-desc">That's what the record fine represented. Stock price rose after the announcement.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="intro">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro__body">
        <h2>What this is</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Big Tech Files</strong> is a reference portal documenting 33 cases of
          privacy, security and ethics violations by the largest technology companies —
          Meta, Google, Apple, Microsoft, Amazon, Uber, TikTok, X (formerly Twitter),
          Clearview AI, Zoom and LinkedIn.
        </p>
        <p>
          Each case is a documentary card based exclusively on regulatory decisions,
          court documents, investigative journalism, academic research and
          whistleblower disclosures. All amounts and dates are verified against
          at least two independent sources.
        </p>

        <h2>Five doors into the data</h2>
        <p>
          The portal has no single narrative path. The homepage presents five equal
          entries into the same 33 cases:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>WHAT</strong> — grid of 33 cases with filters and full-text search</li>
          <li><strong>WHEN</strong> — narrative timeline 2010–2026</li>
          <li><strong>WHERE</strong> — map of regulators and jurisdictions</li>
          <li><strong>WHY</strong> — network graph linking cases, people, companies</li>
          <li><strong>WHO REVEALED IT</strong> — gallery of 12 whistleblowers and journalists</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Privacy of this portal</h2>
        <p>
          A project that documents privacy violations cannot itself violate the privacy
          of its readers. Matryca collects no user data, uses no analytics cookies,
          loads no external trackers. All assets are self-hosted.
        </p>

        <h2>License</h2>
        <p>
          Content is educational material for free use. When citing, please credit:
          <em>Matryca / Big Tech Files, 2026 — matryca.org</em>.
        </p>

        <h2>Status</h2>
        <p class="status">
          The English edition is currently a <strong>preview</strong>. Full translation
          of all 33 case cards (~110,000 words), 4 editorial essays, 12 whistleblower
          profiles and all supporting materials is planned for Phase 4. The Polish
          edition at <a href={url('/')}>matryca.org</a> is complete and up to date.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Page>

<style lang="scss">
  .hero {
    padding-block: var(--space-16) var(--space-12);
    border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--border);
  }

  .hero__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--space-8);
    align-items: start;

    @media (min-width: 900px) {
      grid-template-columns: minmax(0, 1.4fr) minmax(260px, 1fr);
      gap: var(--space-10);
    }
  }

  .hero__body { max-width: 640px; }

  .hero__tagline {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 12px;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-3);
  }

  .hero__title {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: clamp(36px, 6vw, 52px);
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.025em;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-5);
  }

  .hero__lead {
    margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
    max-width: 560px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-2);
  }

  .hero__lead-thesis {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .hero__lead-scope {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.4;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin: 0;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .hero__lead-numbers {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .hero__lead-stamp {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.12em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    margin: var(--space-1) 0 0;
  }

  .hero__actions {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-6);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .hero__notice {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    max-width: 320px;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  .hero__aside {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-5);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
    border-left: 1px solid var(--border);

    @media (max-width: 899px) {
      padding-left: var(--space-4);
      margin-top: var(--space-4);
    }
  }

  .hero__fact {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 4px;
  }

  .hero__fact-value {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 32px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--accent);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero__fact-label {
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: var(--text-tertiary);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .hero__fact-desc {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .intro {
    padding-block: var(--space-12);
  }

  .intro__body {
    max-width: 720px;
  }

  .intro__body h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 26px;
    font-weight: 500;
    line-height: 1.3;
    margin-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-3);
  }

  .intro__body h2:first-of-type {
    margin-top: 0;
  }

  .intro__body p {
    font-size: 17px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
  }

  .intro__body ul {
    margin: var(--space-3) 0 var(--space-4);
    padding-left: var(--space-6);
  }

  .intro__body li {
    font-size: 16px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
  }

  .intro__body strong {
    color: var(--accent);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  .status {
    padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
    background: var(--bg-card);
    border: 0.5px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
    font-size: 15px !important;
  }
</style>
